					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>A fragment of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali on Exodus 18-20.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="120v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Shemot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש שמות </title>
							<title xml:lang="en">The commentary on Exodus</title>
							<note>
								<p>An Arabic translation of the Hebrew text of Ex. 18:1-20:12 and 20:16-22 is embodied, each verse being followed by an Arabic translation.</p>
								<p>Chapters 18:1-20:7 are pointed and accentuated, the rest is unpointed.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of approximately 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>120 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>183</height>
										<width>135</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>120 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end)</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>13 quires (1-11 and 13-14) of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic numerals on the upper margin of the first page, and with Hebrew letters on the lower margin of the last page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>There are lacunae after folios 2, 34, 44, 103 and 117.</p>
									<p>Defective at the end.</p>
									<p>Several folios have been water-damaged and stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="14 15" writtenLines="14 15">
									<p>Visible ruling with a mastara.</p>
									<p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Semi-cursive script of approximately 15th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
